# Documentation Review

You just implemented changes to resolve issue #{{ issue_number }}: **{{ issue_title }}**

Review the project documentation to ensure it reflects the changes you made. Check:

- `CLAUDE.md` — project structure, safety patterns, design principles, configuration docs
- `DECISIONS.md` — architectural decisions (add a new entry if you made a non-obvious design choice)
- `README.md` — if the change affects user-facing behaviour or setup
- `docs/` — any relevant documentation files
- Package-level READMEs (`packages/*/README.md`) — if you modified a specific package

## Instructions

- If the docs are already accurate, do nothing. Not every code change needs a docs update.
- If your changes introduced new configuration, new CLI behaviour, new patterns, or changed existing behaviour, update the relevant docs.
- If you made an architectural decision worth recording (e.g., chose one library over another, picked a specific pattern for a reason), add it to `DECISIONS.md`.
- Keep doc changes minimal and focused. Do not rewrite sections that are already correct.
- Match the existing tone and formatting of each file you edit.
